<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="176" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,151,2021]" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,326,1744,1769]" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">Etymology</emphasis>
. The epithet ‘ 
<taxonomicName box="[493,561,1744,1769]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Ceriana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="176" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="media">
<emphasis box="[493,561,1744,1769]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">media</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’ means intermediate in Latin and refers to the fact that this species has an intermediate morphology between 
<taxonomicName box="[542,713,1780,1805]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Ceriana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="176" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="conopsoides">
<emphasis box="[542,713,1780,1805]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">C. conopsoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[767,928,1780,1805]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Ceriana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="176" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="skevingtoni" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[767,928,1780,1805]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">C. skevingtoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[934,998,1780,1805]" pageId="25" pageNumber="176" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[934,998,1780,1805]" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">sp. n.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,727,1816,1841]" pageId="25" pageNumber="176" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,151,2021]" box="[199,727,1816,1841]" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,287,1816,1841]" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">Biology</emphasis>
. Adults fly from mid April to late July.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="26" lastPageNumber="177" pageId="25" pageNumber="176" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,151,2021]" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,325,1852,1877]" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">Discussion</emphasis>
. The possible synonyms of 
<taxonomicName box="[645,818,1852,1877]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Ceriana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="176" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="conopsoides">
<emphasis box="[645,818,1852,1877]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">C. conopsoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are discussed under that species. The only species not studied and with an imprecise description is 
<taxonomicName box="[652,827,1888,1913]" class="Insecta" family="Anthomyiidae" genus="Musca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="176" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="adunata">
<emphasis box="[652,827,1888,1913]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">Musca adunata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The type locality of this species (Paris, France) is far beyond the distributional range of 
<taxonomicName box="[534,635,1924,1949]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Ceriana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="176" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="media">
<emphasis box="[534,635,1924,1949]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">C. media</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[688,848,1924,1949]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Ceriana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="176" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="skevingtoni">
<emphasis box="[688,848,1924,1949]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">C. skevingtoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The possible synonym of 
<taxonomicName box="[1149,1278,1924,1949]" class="Insecta" family="Anthomyiidae" genus="Musca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="176" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="adunata">
<emphasis box="[1149,1278,1924,1949]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">M. adunata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with either 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Ceriana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="176" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="media">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">C. media</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName box="[256,416,1960,1985]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Ceriana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="176" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="skevingtoni">
<emphasis box="[256,416,1960,1985]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">C. skevingtoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is herewith rejected.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,151,2021]" box="[199,1436,1996,2021]" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">
Several East-Palaearctic 
<taxonomicName box="[478,570,1997,2020]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Ceriana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="176" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[478,570,1997,2020]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">Ceriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species such as 
<taxonomicName authority="Seguy, 1948" authorityName="Seguy" authorityYear="1948" box="[756,1034,1997,2021]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Ceriana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="176" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anceps">
<emphasis box="[756,867,1997,2020]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">C. anceps</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Seguy" box="[882,1025,1997,2021]" pageId="25" pageNumber="176" refString="Seguy, E. (1948) Dipteres nouveaux ou peu connus d'Extreme-Orient. Notes d'entomologie Chinoise, 12, 153 - 172." type="journal article" year="1948">Séguy, 1948</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Shiraki, 1968" authorityName="Shiraki" authorityYear="1968" box="[1046,1354,1996,2021]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Hisamatsumyia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="176" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="japonica">
<emphasis box="[1046,1177,1997,2020]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">C. japonica</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Shiraki" box="[1192,1346,1996,2021]" pageId="25" pageNumber="176" refString="Shiraki, T. (1968) Syrphidae (Insecta) volume III. Fauna Japonica. Biogeographical Society of Japan, Tokyo, 47 plates, 272 pp." type="book" year="1968">Shiraki, 1968</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[1410,1436,1997,2020]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">C.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1436,151,357]" pageId="26" pageNumber="177">
<emphasis box="[151,263,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="177">nigerrima</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Violovitsh" box="[270,456,151,176]" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" refString="Violovitsh, N. A. (1974) Brief survey of palaearctic species of the genus Ceriana Rafinesque, 1815 (Diptera, Syrphidae). Izvestiȳa Sirbirskogo Otdeleniya Akademii Nauk (Biologicheskoi), 1, 81 - 88. [in Russian, with English summary]." type="journal article" year="1974">Violovitsh, 1974</bibRefCitation>
resemble, in overall appearance, 
<taxonomicName box="[831,932,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Ceriana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="media" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[831,932,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="177">C. media</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[939,1002,151,176]" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[939,1002,151,176]" pageId="26" pageNumber="177">sp. n.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1056,1215,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Ceriana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="skevingtoni" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[1056,1215,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="177">C. skevingtoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1222,1286,151,176]" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1222,1286,151,176]" pageId="26" pageNumber="177">sp. n.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, but they can be distinguished from these two by an entirely black scutellum. The Chinese species 
<taxonomicName authority="Shannon, 1925" authorityName="Shannon" authorityYear="1925" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Ceriana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grahami">
<emphasis box="[1118,1314,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="177">Ceriana grahami</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Shannon" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" refString="Shannon, R. C. (1925) The syrphid-flies of the subfamily Ceriodinae in the U. S. National Museum Collection. Insecutor Inscitiae Menstruus, 13, 48 - 52, 53 - 65." type="journal article" year="1925">Shannon, 1925</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, also similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[399,501,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Ceriana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="media" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[399,501,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="177">C. media</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[509,574,223,248]" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[509,574,223,248]" pageId="26" pageNumber="177">sp. n.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[629,790,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Ceriana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="skevingtoni" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[629,790,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="177">C. skevingtoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[798,862,223,248]" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[798,862,223,248]" pageId="26" pageNumber="177">sp. n.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, can be separated from these two by the following unique combination of characters: dorsal surface of head capsule with two yellow maculae that are posterolateral to the ocellar triangle (yellow colour more extended), scutum only with postpronotum and notopleuron yellow, pleuron black except for two yellow maculae and scutellum with a narrow medial yellow fascia.
</paragraph>
